{
  "texts": [
    "For ACER, Bin history reaches an episodic reward of around 0.75; while using the other two replay buffers yields substantially lower episodic rewards and higher variances, in particular for Top-Bottom history.",
    "Top history reaches an episodic reward below 0.3, not reaching above the diversity filter threshold.",
    "ACER with Bin history is the only combination that is able to obtain an average episodic reward comparable to the best on-policy algorithms, but with a slower increase in average episodic reward.",
    "SAC displays a significantly slower increase in average episodic reward than both ACER and the on-policy algorithms.",
    "Figure 11 displays box plots of the number of active molecules and scaffolds, over 11 repeated runs for each combination of off-policy algorithms and replay buffers."
  ]
}